---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro'
import Footer from '../../components/Footer.astro'
import ArticleHeader from '../../components/blog/ArticleHeader.astro'
import ArticleSchema from '../../components/blog/ArticleSchema.astro'
import ArticleCTA from '../../components/blog/ArticleCTA.astro'
import ArticleBottomCTA from '../../components/blog/ArticleBottomCTA.astro'
import RelatedPosts from '../../components/blog/RelatedPosts.astro'
import { Check, X, Star, DollarSign, Zap, Shield, Globe, MessageSquare, Bot, Building2, Settings, Users, Server, TrendingUp } from '@lucide/astro'
import { getPost } from '../../data/blog-posts'

const post = getPost('best-hotel-chatbots')!

const relatedPosts = [
  {
    href: '/blog/free-hotel-chatbot-solutions/',
    title: 'Free Hotel Chatbot Solutions',
    description: 'Compare the best free chatbot options for your hotel.'
  },
  {
    href: '/blog/what-is-hotel-chatbot/',
    title: 'What is a Hotel Chatbot?',
    description: 'Complete guide to hotel chatbots and how they work.'
  },
  {
    href: '/blog/open-source-hotel-chatbot-setup/',
    title: 'Open Source Hotel Chatbot Setup',
    description: 'Deploy a free, self-hosted hotel chatbot step by step.'
  }
]
---

<Layout
  title={post.title}
  description={post.description}
  type="article"
  author={post.author.name}
  publishedTime={post.date}
>
  <ArticleSchema post={post} />

  <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify({
    "@context": "https://schema.org",
    "@type": "FAQPage",
    "mainEntity": [
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "What is the best hotel chatbot in 2026?",
        "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "It depends on your needs and budget. Jack The Butler is the best free and open-source option with full AI capabilities and self-hosting. HiJiffy is best for enterprise hotels needing comprehensive integrations. Asksuite excels for hotel chains with centralized management. Tidio offers the best budget option for small properties testing chatbots for the first time." }
      },
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "How much do hotel chatbots cost?",
        "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "Pricing ranges widely: free and open source (Jack The Butler, $5-30/month hosting), budget options (Tidio, Crisp from $25-95/month), mid-range (Whistle, BookBoost from $100-300/month), and enterprise (HiJiffy, Asksuite from $200-2,000+/month). Most also charge per-room or per-message fees." }
      },
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "Can hotel chatbots integrate with my PMS?",
        "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "Most hotel-specific chatbots integrate with major PMS systems like Opera, Mews, Cloudbeds, and others. General-purpose chatbots (Tidio, Crisp, Zendesk) typically do not offer PMS integration. Always verify your specific PMS is supported before purchasing." }
      },
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "Are free hotel chatbots any good?",
        "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "Open-source solutions like Jack The Butler offer full-featured AI chatbot capabilities for free. Freemium options (Tidio, Crisp) have limited free tiers with conversation caps and missing features. For full AI capabilities without cost, self-hosted open source is the best option." }
      },
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "Which hotel chatbot supports WhatsApp?",
        "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "Jack The Butler, HiJiffy, Asksuite, and Whistle all support WhatsApp Business API natively. Tidio and Crisp offer WhatsApp integration on paid plans only. Chatling, Chatbase, and Zendesk have limited or no WhatsApp support. Since WhatsApp is the most popular messaging channel for international hotel guests, native support should be a key selection criterion." }
      },
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "Do I need technical skills to set up a hotel chatbot?",
        "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "Most cloud-based chatbots (HiJiffy, Asksuite, Tidio) require no technical skills — setup is done through a dashboard. Self-hosted options like Jack The Butler offer one-click deploy that handles the technical setup, so no coding is needed. DIY platforms like Chatbase and Chatling require more configuration." }
      },
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "What is the best chatbot for small hotels?",
        "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "For small hotels (under 50 rooms), the best options are Jack The Butler (free, full-featured AI with self-hosting), Crisp (simple free tier for basic live chat), or Tidio (affordable paid plans with good templates). Avoid enterprise solutions like HiJiffy or Asksuite — their pricing and feature complexity are designed for larger properties and hotel chains." }
      },
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "How do hotel chatbots handle multiple languages?",
        "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "AI-powered chatbots (Jack The Butler, HiJiffy, Asksuite) automatically detect the guest's language and respond naturally in 50+ languages without manual configuration. Rule-based chatbots require manual translation of each conversation flow, which is time-consuming and error-prone. For hotels with international guests, AI-powered multilingual support is essential for providing consistent service quality." }
      }
    ]
  })} />

  <article class="pt-32 pb-24 px-6">
    <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto">
      <ArticleHeader post={post} />

      <!-- Content -->
      <div class="prose prose-lg dark:prose-invert max-w-none">

        <p class="lead text-xl text-neutral-600 dark:text-neutral-400">
          Finding the <strong>best hotel chatbot</strong> is overwhelming. There are enterprise platforms charging thousands per month, generic tools not built for hospitality, and everything in between. We tested and compared the 10 most relevant <a href="/blog/what-is-hotel-chatbot/">hotel chatbot</a> solutions so you don't have to.
        </p>

        <p>
          This guide covers features, pricing, pros and cons, and who each chatbot is best for — whether you run a 10-room B&B or a 500-room resort.
        </p>

        <nav class="not-prose my-8 rounded-xl border border-neutral-200 dark:border-neutral-800 bg-neutral-50 dark:bg-neutral-900 p-6">
          <p class="text-sm font-semibold text-neutral-900 dark:text-neutral-100 mb-3">Table of Contents</p>
          <ol class="text-sm space-y-2 list-decimal list-inside text-neutral-600 dark:text-neutral-400">
            <li><a href="#comparison-overview" class="hover:text-blue-600 dark:hover:text-blue-400">How We Evaluated</a></li>
            <li><a href="#comparison-table" class="hover:text-blue-600 dark:hover:text-blue-400">Quick Comparison Table</a></li>
            <li class="font-medium text-neutral-800 dark:text-neutral-200 pt-1">The 10 Best Hotel Chatbots
              <ol class="mt-2 ml-4 columns-2 gap-x-8 font-normal text-neutral-600 dark:text-neutral-400 list-decimal list-inside space-y-1">
                <li><a href="#jack-the-butler" class="hover:text-blue-600 dark:hover:text-blue-400">Jack The Butler</a></li>
                <li><a href="#hijiffy" class="hover:text-blue-600 dark:hover:text-blue-400">HiJiffy</a></li>
                <li><a href="#asksuite" class="hover:text-blue-600 dark:hover:text-blue-400">Asksuite</a></li>
                <li><a href="#whistle" class="hover:text-blue-600 dark:hover:text-blue-400">Whistle</a></li>
                <li><a href="#bookboost" class="hover:text-blue-600 dark:hover:text-blue-400">BookBoost</a></li>
                <li><a href="#tidio" class="hover:text-blue-600 dark:hover:text-blue-400">Tidio</a></li>
                <li><a href="#crisp" class="hover:text-blue-600 dark:hover:text-blue-400">Crisp</a></li>
                <li><a href="#chatling" class="hover:text-blue-600 dark:hover:text-blue-400">Chatling</a></li>
                <li><a href="#zendesk" class="hover:text-blue-600 dark:hover:text-blue-400">Zendesk</a></li>
                <li><a href="#chatbase" class="hover:text-blue-600 dark:hover:text-blue-400">Chatbase</a></li>
              </ol>
            </li>
            <li><a href="#how-to-choose" class="hover:text-blue-600 dark:hover:text-blue-400">How to Choose</a></li>
            <li><a href="#pricing-breakdown" class="hover:text-blue-600 dark:hover:text-blue-400">Pricing Breakdown by Hotel Size</a></li>
            <li><a href="#faq" class="hover:text-blue-600 dark:hover:text-blue-400">FAQ</a></li>
          </ol>
        </nav>

        <h2 id="comparison-overview">How We Evaluated</h2>

        <p>
          We evaluated each chatbot across six criteria that matter most for hotels:
        </p>

        <ul>
          <li><strong>AI quality</strong> — Natural language understanding vs keyword matching</li>
          <li><strong>Channel support</strong> — WhatsApp, SMS, email, web chat</li>
          <li><strong>Hotel-specific features</strong> — PMS integration, guest profiles, task routing</li>
          <li><strong>Pricing transparency</strong> — Total cost including hidden fees</li>
          <li><strong>Ease of setup</strong> — Time from signup to live</li>
          <li><strong>Data ownership</strong> — Where guest data is stored and who controls it</li>
        </ul>

        <h2 id="comparison-table">Quick Comparison</h2>

      </div>

      <!-- Full Comparison Table -->
      <div class="not-prose my-12 overflow-x-auto">
        <table class="w-full text-left border-collapse text-sm">
          <thead>
            <tr class="border-b border-neutral-200 dark:border-neutral-700">
              <th class="py-3 px-3 font-semibold">#</th>
              <th class="py-3 px-3 font-semibold">Chatbot</th>
              <th class="py-3 px-3 font-semibold">Best For</th>
              <th class="py-3 px-3 font-semibold">Pricing</th>
              <th class="py-3 px-3 font-semibold">AI</th>
              <th class="py-3 px-3 font-semibold">WhatsApp</th>
            </tr>
          </thead>
          <tbody class="text-neutral-600 dark:text-neutral-400">
            <tr class="border-b border-neutral-200 dark:border-neutral-800 bg-emerald-50/50 dark:bg-emerald-500/5">
              <td class="py-3 px-3 font-bold text-emerald-600 dark:text-emerald-400">1</td>
              <td class="py-3 px-3 font-semibold text-neutral-900 dark:text-white">Jack The Butler</td>
              <td class="py-3 px-3">Free & Open Source</td>
              <td class="py-3 px-3"><span class="text-emerald-600 dark:text-emerald-400 font-medium">Free</span></td>
              <td class="py-3 px-3">Claude, GPT, Local</td>
              <td class="py-3 px-3"><Check class="w-4 h-4 text-emerald-500" /></td>
            </tr>
            <tr class="border-b border-neutral-200 dark:border-neutral-800">
              <td class="py-3 px-3 font-bold">2</td>
              <td class="py-3 px-3 font-medium">HiJiffy</td>
              <td class="py-3 px-3">Enterprise</td>
              <td class="py-3 px-3">From $100+/mo</td>
              <td class="py-3 px-3">Proprietary</td>
              <td class="py-3 px-3"><Check class="w-4 h-4 text-emerald-500" /></td>
            </tr>
            <tr class="border-b border-neutral-200 dark:border-neutral-800">
              <td class="py-3 px-3 font-bold">3</td>
              <td class="py-3 px-3 font-medium">Asksuite</td>
              <td class="py-3 px-3">Hotel Chains</td>
              <td class="py-3 px-3">Custom ($200+/mo)</td>
              <td class="py-3 px-3">Proprietary</td>
              <td class="py-3 px-3"><Check class="w-4 h-4 text-emerald-500" /></td>
            </tr>
            <tr class="border-b border-neutral-200 dark:border-neutral-800">
              <td class="py-3 px-3 font-bold">4</td>
              <td class="py-3 px-3 font-medium">Whistle</td>
              <td class="py-3 px-3">Messaging-First</td>
              <td class="py-3 px-3">From $100+/mo</td>
              <td class="py-3 px-3">Basic AI</td>
              <td class="py-3 px-3"><Check class="w-4 h-4 text-emerald-500" /></td>
            </tr>
            <tr class="border-b border-neutral-200 dark:border-neutral-800">
              <td class="py-3 px-3 font-bold">5</td>
              <td class="py-3 px-3 font-medium">BookBoost</td>
              <td class="py-3 px-3">PMS Integration</td>
              <td class="py-3 px-3">Custom pricing</td>
              <td class="py-3 px-3">Proprietary</td>
              <td class="py-3 px-3"><Check class="w-4 h-4 text-emerald-500" /></td>
            </tr>
            <tr class="border-b border-neutral-200 dark:border-neutral-800">
              <td class="py-3 px-3 font-bold">6</td>
              <td class="py-3 px-3 font-medium">Tidio</td>
              <td class="py-3 px-3">Budget Option</td>
              <td class="py-3 px-3">Free / $29+/mo</td>
              <td class="py-3 px-3">Lyro AI</td>
              <td class="py-3 px-3 text-neutral-400">Paid only</td>
            </tr>
            <tr class="border-b border-neutral-200 dark:border-neutral-800">
              <td class="py-3 px-3 font-bold">7</td>
              <td class="py-3 px-3 font-medium">Crisp</td>
              <td class="py-3 px-3">Small Properties</td>
              <td class="py-3 px-3">Free / $25+/mo</td>
              <td class="py-3 px-3">Basic</td>
              <td class="py-3 px-3 text-neutral-400">Paid only</td>
            </tr>
            <tr class="border-b border-neutral-200 dark:border-neutral-800">
              <td class="py-3 px-3 font-bold">8</td>
              <td class="py-3 px-3 font-medium">Chatling</td>
              <td class="py-3 px-3">AI Customization</td>
              <td class="py-3 px-3">Free / $15+/mo</td>
              <td class="py-3 px-3">GPT-based</td>
              <td class="py-3 px-3"><X class="w-4 h-4 text-neutral-400" /></td>
            </tr>
            <tr class="border-b border-neutral-200 dark:border-neutral-800">
              <td class="py-3 px-3 font-bold">9</td>
              <td class="py-3 px-3 font-medium">Zendesk</td>
              <td class="py-3 px-3">All-in-One Support</td>
              <td class="py-3 px-3">From $55+/agent/mo</td>
              <td class="py-3 px-3">Zendesk AI</td>
              <td class="py-3 px-3 text-neutral-400">Add-on</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td class="py-3 px-3 font-bold">10</td>
              <td class="py-3 px-3 font-medium">Chatbase</td>
              <td class="py-3 px-3">DIY Setup</td>
              <td class="py-3 px-3">Free / $19+/mo</td>
              <td class="py-3 px-3">GPT-based</td>
              <td class="py-3 px-3"><X class="w-4 h-4 text-neutral-400" /></td>
            </tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>
      </div>

      <div class="prose prose-lg dark:prose-invert max-w-none">
        <h2 id="jack-the-butler">1. Jack The Butler — Best Free & Open Source</h2>
      </div>

      <!-- #1 Jack The Butler -->
      <div class="not-prose my-12 p-6 rounded-2xl bg-emerald-50 dark:bg-emerald-500/10 border-2 border-emerald-300 dark:border-emerald-500/30">
        <div class="flex items-center justify-between mb-4">
          <div class="flex items-center gap-3">
            <span class="text-2xl font-bold text-emerald-600 dark:text-emerald-400">#1</span>
            <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-emerald-900 dark:text-emerald-100">Jack The Butler</h3>
          </div>
          <span class="px-3 py-1 rounded-full text-xs font-semibold bg-emerald-200 dark:bg-emerald-500/20 text-emerald-800 dark:text-emerald-300">Best Free & Open Source</span>
        </div>
        <p class="text-sm text-emerald-800 dark:text-emerald-200 mb-4">
          <a href="/hotel-chatbot/" class="text-emerald-700 dark:text-emerald-300 hover:underline font-medium">Jack The Butler</a> is the only fully <a href="/blog/free-hotel-chatbot-solutions/">free</a>, <a href="https://github.com/JackTheButler/JackTheButler" class="text-emerald-700 dark:text-emerald-300 hover:underline">open-source</a> hotel chatbot. Self-hosted on your own infrastructure, it gives you full AI capabilities, multi-channel support, and PMS integration with zero per-message fees. Built specifically for hospitality with a staff dashboard, knowledge base, guest memory, and smart escalation.
        </p>
        <div class="grid sm:grid-cols-2 gap-3 mb-4">
          <div class="flex items-center gap-2 text-sm text-emerald-800 dark:text-emerald-200">
            <Check class="w-4 h-4 text-emerald-500 shrink-0" /> <span><a href="/blog/hotel-whatsapp-automation/" class="hover:underline">WhatsApp</a>, SMS, Email, Web Chat</span>
          </div>
          <div class="flex items-center gap-2 text-sm text-emerald-800 dark:text-emerald-200">
            <Check class="w-4 h-4 text-emerald-500 shrink-0" /> <span>Claude, GPT, or Local AI</span>
          </div>
          <div class="flex items-center gap-2 text-sm text-emerald-800 dark:text-emerald-200">
            <Check class="w-4 h-4 text-emerald-500 shrink-0" /> <span>PMS integration</span>
          </div>
          <div class="flex items-center gap-2 text-sm text-emerald-800 dark:text-emerald-200">
            <Check class="w-4 h-4 text-emerald-500 shrink-0" /> <span>Unlimited conversations</span>
          </div>
          <div class="flex items-center gap-2 text-sm text-emerald-800 dark:text-emerald-200">
            <Check class="w-4 h-4 text-emerald-500 shrink-0" /> <span>Self-hosted (your data stays yours)</span>
          </div>
          <div class="flex items-center gap-2 text-sm text-emerald-800 dark:text-emerald-200">
            <Check class="w-4 h-4 text-emerald-500 shrink-0" /> <span>Staff dashboard included</span>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="flex items-center justify-between pt-4 border-t border-emerald-200 dark:border-emerald-500/20">
          <div>
            <span class="text-xs text-emerald-600 dark:text-emerald-400 font-medium">PRICING</span>
            <p class="font-bold text-emerald-900 dark:text-emerald-100">Free (open source) — $5-30/mo hosting</p>
          </div>
          <a href="/hotel-chatbot/" class="px-4 py-2 rounded-full text-sm font-semibold bg-emerald-600 text-white hover:bg-emerald-700 transition-colors">Learn More</a>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="prose prose-lg dark:prose-invert max-w-none">
        <p><strong>Best for:</strong> Any hotel that wants a full-featured <a href="/blog/hotel-virtual-assistant/">AI virtual assistant</a> without ongoing SaaS costs. Particularly strong for independent hotels and properties that value data privacy. See our <a href="/blog/open-source-hotel-chatbot-setup/">setup guide</a> to deploy in under 30 minutes.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="prose prose-lg dark:prose-invert max-w-none">
        <h2 id="hijiffy">2. HiJiffy — Best for Enterprise</h2>
      </div>

      <!-- #2 HiJiffy -->
      <div class="not-prose my-12 p-6 rounded-2xl bg-neutral-50 dark:bg-neutral-900/50 border border-neutral-200 dark:border-neutral-800">
        <div class="flex items-center justify-between mb-4">
          <div class="flex items-center gap-3">
            <span class="text-2xl font-bold text-neutral-400">#2</span>
            <h3 class="text-xl font-bold">HiJiffy</h3>
          </div>
          <span class="px-3 py-1 rounded-full text-xs font-semibold bg-blue-100 dark:bg-blue-500/20 text-blue-700 dark:text-blue-300">Best for Enterprise</span>
        </div>
        <p class="text-sm text-neutral-600 dark:text-neutral-400 mb-4">
          HiJiffy is a well-established hospitality chatbot platform used by large hotel groups across Europe. It offers a proprietary AI engine, extensive PMS integrations, and a multi-property management dashboard. The platform covers the full guest journey from pre-booking to post-stay.
        </p>
        <div class="grid sm:grid-cols-2 gap-3 mb-4">
          <div class="flex items-center gap-2 text-sm">
            <Check class="w-4 h-4 text-emerald-500 shrink-0" /> <span>WhatsApp, Web, Social, SMS</span>
          </div>
          <div class="flex items-center gap-2 text-sm">
            <Check class="w-4 h-4 text-emerald-500 shrink-0" /> <span>Extensive PMS integrations</span>
          </div>
          <div class="flex items-center gap-2 text-sm">
            <Check class="w-4 h-4 text-emerald-500 shrink-0" /> <span>Multi-property support</span>
          </div>
          <div class="flex items-center gap-2 text-sm">
            <X class="w-4 h-4 text-neutral-400 shrink-0" /> <span class="text-neutral-500">No free tier</span>
          </div>
          <div class="flex items-center gap-2 text-sm">
            <X class="w-4 h-4 text-neutral-400 shrink-0" /> <span class="text-neutral-500">Cloud-hosted only</span>
          </div>
          <div class="flex items-center gap-2 text-sm">
            <X class="w-4 h-4 text-neutral-400 shrink-0" /> <span class="text-neutral-500">Per-room pricing adds up</span>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="pt-4 border-t border-neutral-200 dark:border-neutral-800">
          <span class="text-xs text-neutral-500 font-medium">PRICING</span>
          <p class="font-bold">From $100+/month — custom per-room pricing for larger properties</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="prose prose-lg dark:prose-invert max-w-none">
        <p><strong>Best for:</strong> Large hotel groups and chains that need enterprise features, dedicated support, and extensive PMS integrations. The budget needs to support $200-1,000+/month.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="prose prose-lg dark:prose-invert max-w-none">
        <h2 id="asksuite">3. Asksuite — Best for Chains</h2>
      </div>

      <!-- #3 Asksuite -->
      <div class="not-prose my-12 p-6 rounded-2xl bg-neutral-50 dark:bg-neutral-900/50 border border-neutral-200 dark:border-neutral-800">
        <div class="flex items-center justify-between mb-4">
          <div class="flex items-center gap-3">
            <span class="text-2xl font-bold text-neutral-400">#3</span>
            <h3 class="text-xl font-bold">Asksuite</h3>
          </div>
          <span class="px-3 py-1 rounded-full text-xs font-semibold bg-violet-100 dark:bg-violet-500/20 text-violet-700 dark:text-violet-300">Best for Chains</span>
        </div>
        <p class="text-sm text-neutral-600 dark:text-neutral-400 mb-4">
          Asksuite specializes in direct booking conversion for hotel chains. Their AI focuses on capturing booking inquiries, comparing rates with OTAs, and driving guests to book directly. Strong in Latin America and expanding globally.
        </p>
        <div class="grid sm:grid-cols-2 gap-3 mb-4">
          <div class="flex items-center gap-2 text-sm">
            <Check class="w-4 h-4 text-emerald-500 shrink-0" /> <span>WhatsApp, Web, Social</span>
          </div>
          <div class="flex items-center gap-2 text-sm">
            <Check class="w-4 h-4 text-emerald-500 shrink-0" /> <span>Direct booking focus</span>
          </div>
          <div class="flex items-center gap-2 text-sm">
            <Check class="w-4 h-4 text-emerald-500 shrink-0" /> <span>Booking engine integration</span>
          </div>
          <div class="flex items-center gap-2 text-sm">
            <X class="w-4 h-4 text-neutral-400 shrink-0" /> <span class="text-neutral-500">No free tier</span>
          </div>
          <div class="flex items-center gap-2 text-sm">
            <X class="w-4 h-4 text-neutral-400 shrink-0" /> <span class="text-neutral-500">Opaque custom pricing</span>
          </div>
          <div class="flex items-center gap-2 text-sm">
            <X class="w-4 h-4 text-neutral-400 shrink-0" /> <span class="text-neutral-500">Less focus on during-stay</span>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="pt-4 border-t border-neutral-200 dark:border-neutral-800">
          <span class="text-xs text-neutral-500 font-medium">PRICING</span>
          <p class="font-bold">Custom pricing — estimated $200+/month for single properties</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="prose prose-lg dark:prose-invert max-w-none">
        <p><strong>Best for:</strong> Hotel chains focused on increasing direct bookings and reducing OTA dependency. Strongest in markets where WhatsApp is the primary communication channel.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="prose prose-lg dark:prose-invert max-w-none">
        <h2 id="whistle">4. Whistle — Best Messaging-First</h2>
