        <h2 id="faq">Frequently Asked Questions</h2>

        <h3>What is the best hotel chatbot in 2026?</h3>
        <p>
          It depends on your needs. <a href="/hotel-chatbot/">Jack The Butler</a> is the best <a href="/blog/free-hotel-chatbot-solutions/">free</a> and open-source option with full AI capabilities. HiJiffy is best for enterprise hotels. Asksuite excels for hotel chains. Tidio offers the best budget option for small properties testing chatbots.
        </p>

        <h3>How much do hotel chatbots cost?</h3>
        <p>
          Pricing ranges widely: free and open source (Jack The Butler, $5-30/month hosting), budget options (Tidio, Crisp from $25-95/month), mid-range (Whistle, BookBoost from $100-300/month), and enterprise (HiJiffy, Asksuite from $200-2,000+/month). Most also charge per-room or per-message fees.
        </p>

        <h3>Can hotel chatbots integrate with my PMS?</h3>
        <p>
          Most hotel-specific chatbots integrate with major PMS systems like Opera, Mews, Cloudbeds, and others. General-purpose chatbots (Tidio, Crisp, Zendesk) typically do not offer PMS integration. Always verify your specific PMS is supported before purchasing.
        </p>

        <h3>Are free hotel chatbots any good?</h3>
        <p>
          <a href="https://github.com/JackTheButler/JackTheButler">Open-source</a> solutions like <a href="/hotel-chatbot/">Jack The Butler</a> offer full-featured AI chatbot capabilities for free. Freemium options (Tidio, Crisp) have limited free tiers with conversation caps and missing features. For full AI capabilities without cost, <a href="/blog/open-source-hotel-chatbot-setup/">self-hosted open source</a> is the best option.
        </p>

        <h3>Which hotel chatbot supports WhatsApp?</h3>
        <p>
          Jack The Butler, HiJiffy, Asksuite, and Whistle all support <a href="/blog/hotel-whatsapp-automation/">WhatsApp Business API</a>. Tidio and Crisp offer WhatsApp on paid plans only. Chatling, Chatbase, and Zendesk have limited or no WhatsApp support.
        </p>

        <h3>Do I need technical skills to set up a hotel chatbot?</h3>
        <p>
          Most cloud-based chatbots (HiJiffy, Asksuite, Tidio) require no technical skills — setup is done through a dashboard. Self-hosted options like Jack The Butler offer <a href="/blog/open-source-hotel-chatbot-setup/">one-click deploy</a> that handles the technical setup, so no coding is needed. DIY platforms like Chatbase and Chatling require more configuration.
        </p>

        <h3>What is the best chatbot for small hotels?</h3>
        <p>
          For small hotels (under 50 rooms), the best options are <a href="/hotel-chatbot/">Jack The Butler</a> (free, full-featured), Crisp (simple free tier for basic chat), or Tidio (affordable paid plans). Avoid enterprise solutions — their pricing is designed for larger properties.
        </p>

        <h3>How do hotel chatbots handle multiple languages?</h3>
        <p>
          AI-powered chatbots (Jack The Butler, HiJiffy, Asksuite) automatically detect and respond in 50+ languages. Rule-based chatbots require manual translation of each flow. For hotels with international guests, AI-powered multilingual support is essential.
        </p>

